abstract: The United States has allocated $175 million in military aid to the Baltic countries of Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania for 2020, the Estonian defense ministry said Monday.
snippet: The United States has allocated $175 million in military aid to the Baltic countries of Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania for 2020, the Estonian defense ministry said Monday.
lead_paragraph: HELSINKI — The United States has allocated $175 million in military aid to the Baltic countries of Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania for 2020, the Estonian defense ministry said Monday.
headline_main: US Allocates $175 Million in Military Aid to Baltics in 2020
headline_print_headline: US Allocates $175 Million in Military Aid to Baltics in 2020

abstract: U.S. sales of newly built homes increased 1.3% in November from the prior month, a sign that low mortgage rates are pushing up purchases as well as prices.
snippet: U.S. sales of newly built homes increased 1.3% in November from the prior month, a sign that low mortgage rates are pushing up purchases as well as prices.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. sales of newly built homes increased 1.3% in November from the prior month, a sign that low mortgage rates are pushing up purchases as well as prices.
headline_main: US New-Home Sales Rose 1.3% in November.
headline_print_headline: US New-Home Sales Rose 1.3% in November.

abstract: A lauded writer who brought to light stories overshadowed by prejudice. An actress and singer who helped embody the manufactured innocence of the 1950s. A self-made billionaire who rose from a childhood of Depression-era poverty and twice ran for president.

abstract: No one has been arrested following a shooting that left one person dead and seven others injured outside a Thai restaurant in suburban Minneapolis, sheriff's officials said Monday.
snippet: No one has been arrested following a shooting that left one person dead and seven others injured outside a Thai restaurant in suburban Minneapolis, sheriff's officials said Monday.
lead_paragraph: SPRING LAKE PARK, Minn. — No one has been arrested following a shooting that left one person dead and seven others injured outside a Thai restaurant in suburban Minneapolis, sheriff's officials said Monday.
headline_main: No Arrests in Minnesota Shooting That Left 1 Dead, 7 Injured
headline_print_headline: No Arrests in Minnesota Shooting That Left 1 Dead, 7 Injured

abstract: Shahidul Alam, the acclaimed Bangladeshi photojournalist and activist, pushes against the limits of his medium to cast light on what is suppressed or has vanished.
snippet: Shahidul Alam, the acclaimed Bangladeshi photojournalist and activist, pushes against the limits of his medium to cast light on what is suppressed or has vanished.
lead_paragraph: Like Woody Guthrie, who called his guitar an anti-fascist weapon, the Bangladeshi photographer Shahidul Alam has used his camera for 35 years as a tool to advance social justice. He began by documenting street protests in Dhaka, the capital, in the mid-80s, making pictures in the tradition of the Magnum photographers, especially Henri Cartier-Bresson. But over time, he pushed against the natural constraints of a medium that registers what is seen, so that he might illuminate what is suppressed or has vanished.

abstract: An Iowa woman who told police she intentionally ran over a 14-year-old girl because she believed the girl was Mexican has been charged with a hate crime for an incident that occurred shortly after the girl was struck.
snippet: An Iowa woman who told police she intentionally ran over a 14-year-old girl because she believed the girl was Mexican has been charged with a hate crime for an incident that occurred shortly after the girl was struck.
lead_paragraph: CLIVE, Iowa — An Iowa woman who told police she intentionally ran over a 14-year-old girl because she believed the girl was Mexican has been charged with a hate crime for an incident that occurred shortly after the girl was struck.
headline_main: Woman Accused in Racist Attack Is Charged in 2nd Incident
headline_print_headline: Woman Accused in Racist Attack Is Charged in 2nd Incident

abstract: A tiny, isolated community near the Canadian border  known for casting ballots just after the stroke of midnight in presidential elections may need to forfeit that tradition in 2020.
snippet: A tiny, isolated community near the Canadian border  known for casting ballots just after the stroke of midnight in presidential elections may need to forfeit that tradition in 2020.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — A tiny, isolated community near the Canadian border known for casting ballots just after the stroke of midnight in presidential elections may need to forfeit that tradition in 2020.
headline_main: Tiny Dixville Notch May Have to Forfeit Midnight Voting
headline_print_headline: Tiny Dixville Notch May Have to Forfeit Midnight Voting
